(44, 8, 18, 12, 8, 9, 9, 'offered them money', 'Connection of Gifts and Requests', 'This connection highlights the theme of offering gifts in exchange for spiritual or physical benefits. In both passages, individuals present valuable items—money in Acts and camels'' burden in 2 Kings—seeking favor or healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 8, 18, 12, 5, 15, 16, 'offered them money', 'Offerings and Refusal', 'Both passages emphasize the refusal to accept money or gifts in exchange for spiritual blessings. In Acts, Simon offers money for the Holy Ghost, while in 2 Kings, Elisha refuses a blessing from Naaman. This connection highlights the integrity of God''s servants in matters of faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 8, 18, 26, 13, 19, 19, 'offered them money', 'Corruption for Gain', 'This connection highlights the theme of using spiritual authority for personal gain. Both passages emphasize the exploitation of faith for material benefit, with Simon offering money and the false prophets profiting from their lies.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
